WEBVTT

00:02.270 --> 00:04.682
- I DON'T KNOW WHAT TO DO.
SHE GOT INTO A BAD GROUP

00:04.720 --> 00:06.472
IN MINNESOTA,
AND I'M WORRIED ABOUT HER.

00:06.520 --> 00:07.657
- I REALLY LIKE YOU.

00:07.690 --> 00:09.681
I REALLY WANT TO MAKE A GO
OF THIS.

00:09.730 --> 00:11.482
- YOUR MOM TOLD ME
THAT YOU'RE GONNA GO BACK

00:11.520 --> 00:12.589
TO WYOMING WITH HER.

00:12.630 --> 00:15.212
- I DON'T HAVE
ANY OTHER OPTIONS.

00:15.250 --> 00:17.286
- I'M PREGNANT.
- HE DOESN'T KNOW?

00:17.320 --> 00:20.380
- NOT YET.
I JUST STARTED TELLING PEOPLE.

00:20.430 --> 00:23.354
- YOUR DIAGNOSTICS
SHOW MULTIPLE BLOCKAGES.

00:23.400 --> 00:28.463
I'M AFRAID IT'S TIME
TO TALK ABOUT SURGERY.

00:28.510 --> 00:32.059
- IT WAS IN
ANOTHER LIFETIME...

00:32.100 --> 00:35.308
- I WAS TALKING TO SHEILA AGAIN
ABOUT HER HUSBAND'S SURGERY.

00:35.340 --> 00:36.568
YOU KNOW,
HE HAD THE SAME SURGERY

00:36.620 --> 00:37.609
THAT YOU'RE HAVING?
- MM-HMM.

00:37.650 --> 00:40.210
- AND SHE SAID SOME OF THE ROOMS
AT THE HOSPITAL

00:40.240 --> 00:43.300
HAVE BEAUTIFUL VIEWS
OF THE COURTYARD.

00:43.350 --> 00:44.829
- REALLY?
- MM-HMM.

00:44.870 --> 00:47.521
- OH, BOY,
DOESN'T THAT SOUND EXCITING.

00:47.560 --> 00:50.245
WE CAN WATCH THE SQUIRRELS
FORNICATE.

00:50.290 --> 00:51.598
THAT'LL BE A HOOT.

00:51.630 --> 00:53.495
- YOU'RE GONNA BE
AT THE HOSPITAL FOR A FULL DAY

00:53.530 --> 00:57.284
BEFORE THE PROCEDURE, SO I JUST
THINK IT'D BE NICE, YOU KNOW,

00:57.330 --> 00:58.536
YOU HAD A BEAUTIFUL VIEW.

00:58.570 --> 01:00.299
- YOU KNOW WHAT?

01:00.330 --> 01:05.267
THE ONLY VIEW I'M GONNA
NEED IS YOU SITTING NEXT TO ME.

01:05.300 --> 01:09.509
- NOW, LOOK,
YOU'VE SEEN THE CARDS.

01:09.550 --> 01:11.233
- [chuckles]
[door opens]

01:11.270 --> 01:13.898
- HEY, ANYBODY HOME?

01:13.930 --> 01:15.727
- WOW, WHAT A SURPRISE.
- HOW ARE YOU?

01:15.760 --> 01:19.378
- HEY, WOW. HEY, SWEETHEART.

01:19.420 --> 01:21.832
HI.

01:21.870 --> 01:23.280
OH, BABY, COME ON NOW.

01:23.320 --> 01:26.699
HEY, AW.

01:26.740 --> 01:27.764
- YOU'RE GONNA BE FINE.

01:27.810 --> 01:29.903
- COME TO SEE THE BIG GUY
BEFORE HIS BIG DAY.

01:29.950 --> 01:31.668
- WELL, THANKS, CROSBY.

01:31.710 --> 01:33.393
- HI, DADDY.
- SWEETHEART.

01:33.430 --> 01:35.534
- HI. YOU LOOK REALLY GOOD.

01:35.570 --> 01:38.676
- THANKS HONEY. OKAY, OKAY--
- WHAT?

01:38.710 --> 01:40.507
- ENOUGH HUGGING.
IT'S GONNA GET WEIRD.

01:40.540 --> 01:43.168
- I'M GOOD.

01:43.200 --> 01:44.303
WE'RE GOOD. YOU'RE LOOKING GOOD.
- HE DOESN'T LIKE YOU.

01:44.340 --> 01:45.375
- YOU'RE GONNA BE FINE.

01:45.410 --> 01:48.208
I LOVE YOU SO MUCH.

01:48.240 --> 01:49.468
- DON'T MAKE HIM
STRESSED OUT, NOW.

01:49.520 --> 01:50.919
- HE'S ALREADY STRESSED OUT.

01:50.970 --> 01:53.586
- NOW, LOOK, YOU GUYS,
IT'S GONNA BE FINE.

01:53.630 --> 01:56.929
I MEAN,
GOT A 96% SUCCESS RATE.

01:56.970 --> 02:01.179
THAT'S LIKE BA'I'I'ING 900,
SO IT'S GONNA BE FINE, YOU KNOW.

02:01.220 --> 02:02.619
COME ON.

02:02.670 --> 02:05.184
JEEZ--AWW, YOU GUYS.

02:05.220 --> 02:09.668
I'VE GOT FOUR JUST BEAUTIFUL
KIDS,

02:11.570 --> 02:15.267
NINE WONDERFUL GRANDKIDS,

02:15.300 --> 02:16.858
A GREAT GRANDCHILD ON THE WAY.

02:16.890 --> 02:18.334
I MEAN,
COME ON, LET'S CELEBRATE.

02:18.370 --> 02:22.852
LET'S HAVE A PARTY, HUH?

02:22.900 --> 02:24.470
- WHAT?

02:24.520 --> 02:26.169
- I'M PREGNANT.
- WOW, REALLY.

02:26.210 --> 02:31.625
- HEY, CONGRATULATIONS, I GUESS.

02:31.660 --> 02:32.934
- OKAY.
- THAT HAPPENS.

02:32.980 --> 02:35.551
- ONE CLEAN SWEEP.

02:35.600 --> 02:37.283
- HEY, MISTER LOOSE-LIPS.

02:37.320 --> 02:39.459
- OH, YEAH, GOSH, DARN.

02:39.500 --> 02:43.391
WELL, THERE YOU GO, SEE?
AMBER, I AM SO SORRY.

02:43.430 --> 02:44.749
I MEAN, I JUST PUT MY FOOT
IN MY MOUTH--

02:44.780 --> 02:45.940
- DON'T BE.
- I JUST BLURTED OUT--

02:45.990 --> 02:47.389
- DON'T BE.
- HUH?

02:47.440 --> 02:48.259
- HONESTLY,
I THOUGHT IT WAS GREAT.

02:48.300 --> 02:49.267
- OH BROTHER.

02:49.300 --> 02:50.369
- I WAS, LIKE, EXTREMELY
STRESSED

02:50.410 --> 02:52.366
ABOUT HAVING TO TELL EVERYBODY
ANYWAY,

02:52.410 --> 02:53.786
AND YOU DID IT FOR ME.

02:53.820 --> 02:55.993
BESIDES, IT'S A GREAT STORY
WE'LL ALWAYS HAVE.

02:56.030 --> 02:58.203
- GOD.

02:58.240 --> 03:01.721
- HEY, I HAVE SOMETHING
I WANT TO SHOW YOU.

03:10.430 --> 03:12.421
- OH, MY.

03:12.460 --> 03:17.705
WHY, HE'S BEAUTIFUL, I MEAN--

03:17.740 --> 03:20.629
- GRANDPA, YOU KNOW IT
COULD POSSIBLY BE A GIRL, RIGHT?

03:20.680 --> 03:22.955
THAT'S OKAY?
- WELL, YEAH. I MEAN,

03:22.990 --> 03:26.232
HE, SHE, IT DOESN'T MA'I'I'ER.

03:26.270 --> 03:28.409
IT'S YOUR BABY.

03:32.690 --> 03:36.968
SO HOW'S RYAN DOING
WITH ALL THIS?

03:37.000 --> 03:41.380
- UH, I HAVEN'T--
I HAVEN'T TALKED TO HIM YET.

03:41.420 --> 03:43.422
I KNOW--I KNOW THAT I HAVE TO,

03:43.460 --> 03:46.384
AND I'M--I WILL.

03:51.610 --> 03:53.328
HERE, NO, YOU KEEP IT.
- NO, HONEY.

03:53.370 --> 03:56.703
NAH, LOOK IT, SWEETHEART,

03:56.750 --> 04:00.811
I'M GONNA BE THERE
TO SEE THIS CHILD BORN, OKAY?

04:00.860 --> 04:04.068
I'M GONNA
HOLD HIM OR HER...

04:04.100 --> 04:08.343
IN MY ARMS.

04:08.380 --> 04:10.302
I PROMISE.

04:10.350 --> 04:15.549
SO YOU KEEP THAT PICTURE.

04:15.600 --> 04:17.659
- OKAY.

04:17.700 --> 04:22.421
- AND YOU SHOW IT TO RYAN.

04:22.460 --> 04:25.395
- YEAH.

04:25.430 --> 04:26.840
I'M SO SCARED.

04:26.880 --> 04:29.462
- OH, I GET IT.
I MEAN, I GET THE FEAR,

04:29.510 --> 04:31.011
YOU KNOW, AND BEING SCARED.

04:31.060 --> 04:33.642
MY GOD, I'VE BEEN GOING THROUGH
IT THE LAST COUPLE OF DAYS.

04:33.680 --> 04:35.056
- OH, GOD.

04:35.100 --> 04:36.783
- BUT HE NEEDS TO KNOW,
SWEETHEART.

04:36.820 --> 04:38.549
- I KNOW.
- YEAH.

04:38.580 --> 04:41.094
- AND, YOU KNOW, WITH YOU,

04:41.140 --> 04:42.368
AND WHAT YOU'RE GOING THROUGH,

04:42.420 --> 04:46.413
YOU KNOW, LIKE,
I KNOW IT'S SCARY,

04:46.450 --> 04:49.101
BUT YOU'RE GONNA GET THROUGH IT
WITH SUCH STRENGTH

04:49.150 --> 04:50.549
BECAUSE OF HOW STRONG YOU ARE,

04:50.600 --> 04:54.422
AND WE ALL GET OUR STRENGTH
FROM YOU.

04:54.460 --> 04:59.466
SO YOU'RE GONNA BE TOTALLY FINE.

05:00.430 --> 05:03.319
IT'S GONNA BE OKAY.

05:05.850 --> 05:07.738
- AH, BOY,
I WISH YOU WERE MY DOCTOR.

05:07.790 --> 05:10.406
- [laughs]

05:10.440 --> 05:12.123
- OH, GOLLY, AMBER,

05:12.170 --> 05:15.822
YOU'RE AN AMAZING GIRL,
SWEETHEART.

05:15.860 --> 05:17.031
- UH-UH.

05:17.070 --> 05:19.038
- MM-HMM.

05:19.070 --> 05:21.584
- MAY GOD BLESS
AND KEEP YOU ALWAYS

05:21.630 --> 05:24.144
AND MAY YOUR WISHES
ALL COME TRUE

05:24.180 --> 05:26.455
MAY YOU ALWAYS DO
FOR OTHERS

05:26.490 --> 05:28.936
AND LET OTHERS DO FOR YOU

05:28.980 --> 05:31.699
MAY YOU BUILD A LADDER
TO THE STARS

05:31.740 --> 05:33.492
AND CLIMB ON EVERY RUNG

05:33.540 --> 05:35.679
AND MAY YOU STAY

05:35.710 --> 05:38.508
FOREVER YOUNG

05:38.540 --> 05:41.054
MAY YOU GROW UP
TO BE RIGHTEOUS

05:41.090 --> 05:43.399
MAY YOU GROW UP
TO BE TRUE

05:43.440 --> 05:45.817
MAY YOU ALWAYS KNOW
THE TRUTH

05:45.860 --> 05:48.169
AND SEE THE LIGHT
SURROUNDING YOU

05:48.200 --> 05:50.657
MAY YOU ALWAYS BE
COURAGEOUS

05:50.690 --> 05:53.033
STAND UPRIGHT
AND BE STRONG

05:53.070 --> 05:54.958
AND MAY YOU STAY

05:55.000 --> 05:58.413
FOREVER YOUNG

05:58.460 --> 06:00.075
MAY YOU STAY

06:00.110 --> 06:02.931
FOREVER YOUNG

06:06.950 --> 06:08.497
- HEY.
- CAN I COME IN?

06:08.540 --> 06:10.701
- YEAH.
- THIS YOUR NEW ROOM?

06:10.740 --> 06:13.015
- OH, YEAH.
THIS IS IT.

06:13.060 --> 06:15.711
- WOW, IT'S NICE.

06:15.750 --> 06:17.854
BROUGHT YOU COFFEE.

06:17.890 --> 06:20.541
ASSUMING YOU GOT MY TEXT.

06:20.580 --> 06:24.129
- YEAH, I GOT ABOUT 15
BEFORE THAT, YEAH.

06:24.170 --> 06:26.889
- I'M SORRY.
I SHOULD'VE--

06:26.930 --> 06:29.751
I SHOULD'VE COME OVER THE SECOND
THAT EVERYBODY KNEW.

06:29.800 --> 06:32.143
I SHOULD'VE--
I SHOULD'VE TOLD YOU, FIRST.

06:32.180 --> 06:36.105
LIKE, YOU'RE THE CLOSEST PERSON
TO ME, AND SOMEHOW,

06:36.150 --> 06:39.699
THAT MADE IT THE SCARIEST
TO TELL YOU ABOUT.

06:39.740 --> 06:40.832
- AMBER, I TOTALLY--

06:40.880 --> 06:42.848
I TOTALLY UNDERSTAND.

06:42.880 --> 06:43.972
IT'S TOTALLY FINE.

06:44.020 --> 06:47.672
I'M JUST--I WANNA KNOW
HOW YOU'RE DOING, YOU KNOW?

06:47.710 --> 06:49.439
- OKAY.
- WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO?

06:49.470 --> 06:50.778
WHAT'S RYAN SAYING ABOUT IT?

06:50.820 --> 06:53.926
- UH, WELL, THAT'S KIND OF WHAT
I CAME HERE TO TALK

06:53.960 --> 06:56.849
TO YOU ABOUT, ACTUALLY, UM--

06:56.890 --> 06:58.710
UH, HE DOESN'T KNOW YET,

06:58.760 --> 07:03.242
AND I JUST WOKE UP FEELING
LIKE I HAD TO TELL HIM TODAY,

07:03.280 --> 07:07.205
SO I JUST WAS WONDERING
IF I COULD BORROW YOUR CAR,

07:07.250 --> 07:09.525
BECAUSE MINE'LL NEVER
MAKE IT TO WYOMING.

07:09.560 --> 07:10.868
- ARE YOU TRYING TO DRIVE THERE?

07:10.910 --> 07:13.526
- YEAH, I JUST FEEL
LIKE I NEED TO, YOU KNOW,

07:13.570 --> 07:14.878
TELL HIM TO HIS FACE, SO--

07:14.910 --> 07:16.878
- I MEAN, CAN'T YOU CALL HIM,
OR SOMETHING, OR--

07:16.910 --> 07:19.913
- I FEEL LIKE I OWE IT TO HIM
TO TALK TO HIM,

07:19.950 --> 07:22.839
PERSON-TO-PERSON, ABOUT THIS.
- YOU DON'T OWE HIM ANYTHING.

07:22.890 --> 07:26.121
- OKAY, DREW, THIS IS SOMETHING
THAT I HAVE TO DO,

07:26.160 --> 07:29.641
AND WHETHER I BORROW YOUR CAR
OR SOMEONE ELSE'S,

07:29.690 --> 07:30.952
I'M GONNA GO UP THERE, SO--

07:31.000 --> 07:33.093
- I'M JUST--
I'M GOING UP THERE WITH YOU.

07:33.140 --> 07:34.858
- WHAT?
- I'M NOT GONNA LET YOU

07:34.900 --> 07:36.106
GO UP THERE AND TALK TO HIM--
- YOU DON'T HAVE TO GO WITH ME.

07:36.140 --> 07:38.176
- YEAH, I KNOW, BUT I DON'T WANT
YOU TO GO UP THERE ALONE.

07:38.210 --> 07:40.132
- FOUND A PIECE OF ME

07:40.180 --> 07:41.272
- I GO'I'I'A CHANGE REALLY QUICK.

07:41.320 --> 07:43.834
- STARING AT THE SEA

07:43.870 --> 07:48.000
- DAD?

07:48.050 --> 07:50.837
DAD?
- MMM.

07:50.880 --> 07:53.110
- DAD?
- YEAH, YEAH, HOLD ON A SECOND.

07:53.160 --> 07:54.775
I JUST FIGURED OUT
THIS DAMN LIGHTING.

07:54.810 --> 07:55.947
- YOU SAID
YOU'D TAKE ME SHOPPING.

07:55.990 --> 07:58.879
- COME ON.

07:58.920 --> 07:59.909
- DOES HE TUNE YOU OUT TOO,

07:59.960 --> 08:02.747
OR IS IT JUST ME?

08:02.790 --> 08:05.611
- HUH? TUNE ME OUT?

08:05.650 --> 08:07.515
OH, HE DOES, YES. OH, YES.

08:07.550 --> 08:08.824
- WELL, WILL YOU PLEASE TELL HIM

08:08.860 --> 08:10.612
THAT HE'S SUPPOSED TO TAKE ME
TO THE MALL? HE'S IGNORING ME.

08:10.660 --> 08:11.752
- YES, I WILL. HANK?
- I'M NOT IGNORING YOU.

08:11.800 --> 08:12.653
FIVE MINUTES, THAT'S IT.
FIVE MINUTES.

08:12.690 --> 08:14.965
- YOU SAID THAT,
LIKE, FIVE HOURS AGO.

08:15.010 --> 08:16.796
GOD, I'M--
I'M SICK OF BEING STUCK HERE.

08:16.840 --> 08:18.796
- HANK? YOU KNOW WHAT?
I'M SICK OF BEING STUCK HERE,

08:18.840 --> 08:21.525
SO LET'S GO ACROSS THE STREET
TO THE DRUG STORE.

08:21.570 --> 08:23.288
IT'S NOT THE MALL, BUT THEY'VE
GOT A GREAT SELECTION

08:23.330 --> 08:25.844
OF LIP GLOSS. YOU WANT TO GO?
- GREAT.

08:25.880 --> 08:27.256
- ALL RIGHT, WELL,
I'LL TAKE THAT AS A YES.

08:27.290 --> 08:29.292
HEY, HANK,
WE'RE LEAVING FOR A LITTLE BIT.

08:29.330 --> 08:31.537
GONNA DO SOME SECRET GIRL STUFF.

08:31.580 --> 08:32.979
HAN K, REGISTER.

08:33.020 --> 08:35.671
REGISTER, HANK.

08:35.720 --> 08:38.689
- YEAH.
- OKAY, TALK TO YOU LATER.

08:38.720 --> 08:40.540
- YOU GUYS GOING?

08:40.580 --> 08:42.059
- OKAY, ADAM
JUST TALKED TO MY MOM.

08:42.100 --> 08:44.580
THEY HAVEN'T EVEN
TAKEN HIM INTO HIS ROOM YET.

08:44.620 --> 08:46.656
WHY IS THIS TAKING FOREVER.

08:46.690 --> 08:48.100
- I WOULDN'T WORRY ABOUT IT.
YOUR OLD MAN'S A TOUGH GUY.

08:48.140 --> 08:51.212
HE'S GONNA BE ALL RIGHT.

08:51.250 --> 08:53.036
WELL, I MEAN, HE SEEMS TOUGH,

08:53.080 --> 08:55.048
YOU KNOW, FROM WHAT YOU'VE TOLD
ME ABOUT HIM.

08:55.080 --> 08:56.809
AND THAT ONE TIME I MET HIM,
HE SEEMED TOUGH AS HELL.

08:56.840 --> 08:58.808
- WHEN DID YOU MEET HIM?

08:58.840 --> 09:00.808
- YOU DON'T REMEMBER.
- YOU DID NOT MEET MY DAD.

09:00.850 --> 09:02.602
- I DISTINCTLY REMEMBER
THAT I DID NOT

09:02.640 --> 09:04.676
INTRODUCE YOU TO MY PARENTS
BECAUSE MY DAD HAS A WAY

09:04.710 --> 09:07.816
OF MAKING INTRODUCTIONS
TO BOYFRIENDS VERY MEMORABLE.

09:07.850 --> 09:09.124
- MM-MM, YOU DON'T REMEMBER
BECAUSE IT WAS BEFORE

09:09.160 --> 09:10.787
WE WERE DATING.

09:10.820 --> 09:14.608
IT WAS OUR FRESHMEN STUDY GROUP
IN YOUR DORM ROOM.

09:14.650 --> 09:16.026
AHH, YOU REMEMBER NOW,
DON'T YOU?

09:16.070 --> 09:19.301
- YES,
I COMPLETELY BLOCKED THAT OUT.

09:19.350 --> 09:21.625
- MM-HMM. HE COULDN'T FIGURE OUT
WHERE YOU WERE, SO HE WAS JUST

09:21.660 --> 09:23.059
WALKING AROUND THE COMPLEX,
SCREAMING YOUR NAME.

09:23.110 --> 09:27.217
- YELLING, YEAH,
"JULIA, DAMN IT!"

09:27.250 --> 09:28.103
- AND THEN,
HE FOUND YOUR COMPLEX,

09:28.150 --> 09:29.799
AND HE WALKED
RIGHT IN YOUR APARTMENT

09:29.840 --> 09:31.831
WITH YOUR FINALS SURVIVAL KIT.
- CANDY.

09:31.880 --> 09:33.802
- A HUGE BOX.
- HUGE BOX OF CANDY.

09:33.840 --> 09:35.876
- MM-HMM, AND A "GO CAL"
T-SHIRT, IF I RECALL CORRECT LY.

09:35.920 --> 09:38.388
- MM-HMM,
THAT IS DEFINITELY MY DAD.

09:38.430 --> 09:40.887
HE WILL NOT, TO THIS DAY,
ADMIT THAT I WENT TO STANFORD.

09:40.920 --> 09:42.126
- I THOUGHT IT WAS PRE'ITY COOL
THAT YOUR OLD MAN

09:42.160 --> 09:46.369
DROVE ACROSS THE BAY JUST
TO BRING YOU A BOX OF TWIZZLERS.

09:48.930 --> 09:50.648
- MY FAVORITE STUDY SNACK.
- I KNOW.

09:50.690 --> 09:51.782
IT STILL IS.
- I KNOW.

09:51.830 --> 09:53.684
- HOW DO YOU REMEMBER THIS?

09:53.730 --> 09:54.958
THIS CRAZY DETAIL.

09:55.000 --> 09:58.345
- IT TOOK ME SIX MONTHS TO GET
THE COURAGE TO ASK YOU OUT.

09:58.390 --> 10:00.244
I WAITED FIVE DATES.

10:00.280 --> 10:01.724
YOU BLEW ME OFF
BECAUSE YOU TOLD ME

10:01.770 --> 10:03.101
THAT YOU HAD TO FOCUS ON SCHOOL.

10:03.150 --> 10:04.424
- I WAS VERY FOCUSED.

10:04.460 --> 10:07.145
- YOU WERE, INDEED, VERY, VERY
FOCUSED, AND VERY ADORABLE TOO.

10:07.190 --> 10:11.320
[phone ringing]
- IS IT HIM AGAIN.

10:11.360 --> 10:12.634
- YOU SHOULD TAKE
THAT PHONE CALL.

10:12.680 --> 10:14.910
- YEP.
- GIVE ME A KISS.

10:14.950 --> 10:15.848
- BYE.
- I'LL SEE YOU LATER.

10:15.890 --> 10:18.814
- OKAY.

10:18.850 --> 10:21.159
AHEM. HEY.

10:21.200 --> 10:24.681
[pop music playing]

10:24.720 --> 10:26.824
- HOW ARE YOU LIKING
THE NEW SCHOOL?

10:26.860 --> 10:31.934
- IT'S OKAY.
- YEAH, WELL, IT PROBABLY

10:31.970 --> 10:33.892
TAKES A LITTLE TIME, YOU KNOW,
TO GET USED TO IT.

10:33.940 --> 10:35.862
- IT'S--IT'S OKAY.

10:35.910 --> 10:38.902
LIKE, YOU DON'T HAVE TO TRY
AND MAKE CONVERSATION WITH ME.

10:38.940 --> 10:42.899
WE CAN JUST SHOP.

10:42.950 --> 10:45.157
- OH, ALL RIGHT. HEY, HELP
ME PICK A COLOR, THOUGH.

10:45.190 --> 10:46.737
WHAT DO YOU THINK OF THAT?

10:46.780 --> 10:48.361
IT'S KIND OF A CLASSIC.

10:48.400 --> 10:50.152
- RED'S FOR OLD PEOPLE.

10:50.200 --> 10:51.747
- RED IS--RED IS FOR OLD PEOPLE.

10:51.780 --> 10:54.192
OKAY, WELL,
I DON'T WANT THAT ONE, THEN.

10:54.230 --> 10:57.199
WHAT IS--WHAT IS A GOOD COLOR?

10:57.240 --> 11:01.688
- YOU SHOULD GET THE RED.

11:01.730 --> 11:02.719
_ 1--

11:10.220 --> 11:15.248
- RUBY, DID YOU
WANT TO BUY A LIP GLOSS?

11:15.290 --> 11:17.941
- NAH, I'M GOOD.

11:24.160 --> 11:25.843
- WOW, LOOK AT THIS.

11:25.890 --> 11:27.949
THIS IS A BETTER VIEW
THAN THE COURTYARD.

11:27.990 --> 11:29.878
- OKAY, MR. BRAVERMAN,

11:29.930 --> 11:32.160
THIS WILL BE YOUR HOME WHILE YOU
COME OFF YOUR BLOOD THINNERS.

11:32.200 --> 11:34.259
THERE IS YOUR GOWN. YOU
CAN GO 'HEAD AND PUT THAT ON,

11:34.310 --> 11:36.926
AND PUT YOUR PERSONAL BELONGINGS
INTO THE PLASTIC BAG.

11:36.970 --> 11:40.929
YOUR CLOTHING, YOUR JEWELRY,
DON'T FORGET YOUR WEDDING RING,

11:40.970 --> 11:44.098
AND--WE'LL GET YOUR IV GOING,
OKAY?

11:44.150 --> 11:45.458
- WHAT ARE YOU GONNA
DO WITH MY STUFF?

11:45.490 --> 11:46.866
- I'M SORRY,
WHAT'S THAT, MR. BRAVERMAN?

11:46.910 --> 11:47.934
- WHERE YOU GONNA PUT MY STUFF?

11:47.980 --> 11:53.213
